The paper discusses a framework for managing multiple maps of different types, which is relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The framework is capable of handling semantic polygonal layers, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and autonomous exploration, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents an algorithm for generating semantic layers from RGB-D images, which further supports the relevance to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the framework to autonomous exploration, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
